---
import '@fontsource-variable/space-grotesk';
import '@fontsource-variable/newsreader';
import '@fontsource/ibm-plex-sans/400.css';
import '@fontsource/ibm-plex-sans/600.css';
import '../../styles/scripto-standalone.css';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="SCRIPTO standalone: parchment-toned writing and analysis surface for deterministic packet building."
    />
    <meta name="theme-color" content="#6f4b1f" />
    <title>SCRIPTO | Parchment Builder Surface</title>
  </head>
  <body class="scripto-standalone">
    <div class="scripto-shell">
      <header class="scripto-header">
        <a class="scripto-brand" href="/scripto/">
          <span class="scripto-mark">SCRIPTO</span>
          <span class="scripto-tagline">Deterministic Packet Instrument</span>
        </a>
        <nav class="scripto-nav" aria-label="SCRIPTO navigation">
          <a href="/scriptorium/">Open full app</a>
          <a href="/projects/scriptorium/">Project record</a>
          <a href="/contact/">Contact</a>
        </nav>
      </header>

      <main class="scripto-main">
        <section class="scripto-hero" aria-labelledby="scripto-title">
          <div class="scripto-hero-grid">
            <div>
              <p class="scripto-eyebrow">Deterministic writing app</p>
              <h1 id="scripto-title">A control surface for manuscripts under pressure.</h1>
              <p>
                SCRIPTO is not a text generator. It is a packet builder that forces every draft through an explicit
                sequence: intake, recursive testing, control assignment, and bounded export.
              </p>
              <p>
                The objective is simple and strict: make claims travel only as far as their visible evidence trail can
                carry them.
              </p>
              <div class="scripto-actions">
                <a class="scripto-button primary" href="/scriptorium/#scriptorium-builder">Open builder</a>
                <a class="scripto-button secondary" href="/scriptorium/#scriptorium-method">Method commitments</a>
              </div>
            </div>

            <aside class="scripto-meta-panel" aria-label="Instrument frame">
              <h2>Instrument Frame</h2>
              <ul>
                <li><span>Mode</span><strong>Packet-first drafting</strong></li>
                <li><span>Input</span><strong>Manuscript, quotes, and references</strong></li>
                <li><span>Control</span><strong>Fail-closed claim discipline</strong></li>
                <li><span>Output</span><strong>Reviewable markdown packet</strong></li>
              </ul>
            </aside>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="scripto-section" aria-labelledby="scripto-flow-title">
          <div class="scripto-section-head">
            <p class="scripto-kicker">Packet flow</p>
            <h2 id="scripto-flow-title">From intake to export, one visible manuscript chain.</h2>
          </div>

          <div class="scripto-grid" aria-label="SCRIPTO workflow">
            <article class="scripto-card">
              <p class="scripto-step">01</p>
              <h3>Packet Setup</h3>
              <p>Set governing object, consequence domain, and recursive pressure before any polish pass begins.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="scripto-card">
              <p class="scripto-step">02</p>
              <h3>Recursive Checks</h3>
              <p>Run contradiction and overclaim checks so revision pressure stays accountable to the manuscript body.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="scripto-card">
              <p class="scripto-step">03</p>
              <h3>Control Assignment</h3>
              <p>Attach finding, owner, evidence requirement, and review interval to each load-bearing claim path.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="scripto-card">
              <p class="scripto-step">04</p>
              <h3>Export Layer</h3>
              <p>Export a bounded packet with readiness call, controls, and disclosure language ready for human review.</p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="scripto-section" aria-labelledby="scripto-control-title">
          <div class="scripto-section-head">
            <p class="scripto-kicker">Control lattice</p>
            <h2 id="scripto-control-title">What SCRIPTO enforces before a packet can travel.</h2>
          </div>

          <div class="scripto-grid scripto-grid-2" aria-label="SCRIPTO control architecture">
            <article class="scripto-card">
              <h3>Support Corroboration</h3>
              <p>Separate direct evidence from supported inference and unresolved uncertainty in every revision cycle.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="scripto-card">
              <h3>Recursive Triangulation</h3>
              <p>Require pre-pass and post-pass checks so each rewrite keeps or strengthens support anchors.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="scripto-card">
              <h3>Henry Reviewer Stack</h3>
              <p>Stress-test the manuscript with supportive, cold-method, and harsh review pressure before promotion.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="scripto-card">
              <h3>Bounded Conclusion</h3>
              <p>Force an explicit limit statement and disclosure language before external circulation.</p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="scripto-ledger" aria-labelledby="scripto-ledger-title">
          <article class="scripto-sheet" aria-label="Packet example">
            <h2 id="scripto-ledger-title">Live packet ledger</h2>
            <p class="scripto-sheet-subhead">Packet status snapshot</p>
            <p class="sheet-line">Object: governance brief packet</p>
            <p class="sheet-line">Readiness call: revise before external review</p>
            <p class="sheet-line">Evidence floor: source-bound references and unresolved unknowns</p>
            <p class="sheet-line">Controls: owner + evidence + review interval defined</p>
            <p class="sheet-line">Output: structured markdown, disclosure-ready</p>
          </article>

          <aside class="scripto-margin-note" aria-label="Margin notes">
            <h3>Margin Notes</h3>
            <p>Each pass keeps three lanes visible: verified evidence, supported inference, and unresolved unknowns.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Keep source classes explicit.</li>
              <li>Capture contradictions before closure.</li>
              <li>Name the control owner before handoff.</li>
              <li>Export only bounded claims.</li>
            </ul>
            <a class="scripto-note-link" href="/projects/scriptorium/">Open project record</a>
          </aside>
        </section>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
